{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143465937,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_AbZetxDSIHnq2JggVjg2nveU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/003-router-rewire/spec.md","offset":40,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/003-router-rewire/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n40: ## 1. METADATA\n41: \n42: | Field | Value |\n43: |-------|-------|\n44: | **Level** | 1 |\n45: | **Priority** | P1 |\n46: | **Status** | Completed with YAML asset gap reported |\n47: | **Created** | 2026-06-10 |\n48: | **Branch** | `main` |\n49: | **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n50: | **Completion** | 100% |\n51: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n56: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n57: \n58: ### Problem Statement\n59: Memory Commands needs a scoped router rewire phase so presentation extraction can proceed without mixing implementation, routing, and display-contract decisions.\n60: \n61: ### Purpose\n62: Rewrite each command.md as a thin router that points to the workflow file and the presentation Markdown file, preserving behavior and leaving no presentation contract inline.\n63: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n68: ## 3. SCOPE\n69: \n70: ### In Scope\n71: - Thin-router command.md contract.\n72: - Workflow-file routing references.\n73: - Presentation Markdown routing references.\n74: - Family command scope: `.opencode/commands/memory/*.md` and the workflow asset YAML files those commands route to.\n75: \n76: \n77: ### Out of Scope\n78: - Source-code changes.\n79: - Command.md rewrites during scaffold.\n80: - Workflow YAML edits during scaffold.\n81: - Implementation work beyond the Planned scaffold.\n82: \n83: ### Files to Change\n84: Planned future implementation scope; this scaffold only creates spec docs and metadata.\n85: \n86: | File Path | Change Type | Description |\n87: |-----------|-------------|-------------|\n88: | `.opencode/commands/memory/*.md` | Future Review/Modify | Family command and workflow asset scope for this leaf |\n89: | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/**/*.yaml` | Future Review/Modify | Family command and workflow asset scope for this leaf |\n90: | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/**/*.yml` | Future Review/Modify | Family command and workflow asset scope for this leaf |\n91: | Dedicated presentation Markdown files | Future Create/Modify | Presentation contracts for startup questions, dashboards, and results display |\n92: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n97: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n98: \n99: ### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)\n100: \n101: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n102: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n103: | R1 | Preserve workflow behavior | Planned changes do not alter command routing semantics |\n104: | R2 | Keep presentation contract explicit | Startup questions, dashboard layouts, and results-display rules are discoverable through Markdown presentation contracts |\n105: \n106: ### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n107: \n108: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n109: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n110: | R3 | Keep scope family-local | Work is limited to memory commands command surfaces and their presentation contracts |\n111: | R4 | Verify with strict spec validation | Leaf folder validates before implementation handoff |\n112: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n117: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n118: \n119: - The leaf has a clear implementation handoff for router rewire.\n120: - The leaf preserves the packet principle: thin command routers plus dedicated Markdown presentation contracts.\n121: - Strict spec validation passes for this folder.\n122: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n127: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n128: \n129: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n\n(Showing lines 40-129 of 142. Use offset=130 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 1 |\n| **Priority** | P1 |\n| **Status** | Completed with YAML asset gap reported |\n| **Created** | 2026-06-10 |\n| **Branch** | `main` |\n| **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n| **Completion** | 100% |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\nMemory Commands needs a scoped router rewire phase so presentation extraction can proceed without mixing implementation, routing, and display-contract decisions.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/003-router-rewire/spec.md","text":"## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 1 |\n| **Priority** | P1 |\n| **Status** | Completed with YAML asset gap reported |\n| **Created** | 2026-06-10 |\n| **Branch** | `main` |\n| **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n| **Completion** | 100% |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\nMemory Commands needs a scoped router rewire phase so presentation extraction can proceed without mixing implementation, routing, and display-contract decisions.\n\n### Purpose\nRewrite each command.md as a thin router that points to the workflow file and the presentation Markdown file, preserving behavior and leaving no presentation contract inline.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Thin-router command.md contract.\n- Workflow-file routing references.\n- Presentation Markdown routing references.\n- Family command scope: `.opencode/commands/memory/*.md` and the workflow asset YAML files those commands route to.\n\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Source-code changes.\n- Command.md rewrites during scaffold.\n- Workflow YAML edits during scaffold.\n- Implementation work beyond the Planned scaffold.\n\n### Files to Change\nPlanned future implementation scope; this scaffold only creates spec docs and metadata.\n\n| File Path | Change Type | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| `.opencode/commands/memory/*.md` | Future Review/Modify | Family command and workflow asset scope for this leaf |\n| `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/**/*.yaml` | Future Review/Modify | Family command and workflow asset scope for this leaf |\n| `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/**/*.yml` | Future Review/Modify | Family command and workflow asset scope for this leaf |\n| Dedicated presentation Markdown files | Future Create/Modify | Presentation contracts for startup questions, dashboards, and results display |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| R1 | Preserve workflow behavior | Planned changes do not alter command routing semantics |\n| R2 | Keep presentation contract explicit | Startup questions, dashboard layouts, and results-display rules are discoverable through Markdown presentation contracts |\n\n### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| R3 | Keep scope family-local | Work is limited to memory commands command surfaces and their presentation contracts |\n| R4 | Verify with strict spec validation | Leaf folder validates before implementation handoff |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- The leaf has a clear implementation handoff for router rewire.\n- The leaf preserves the packet principle: thin command routers plus dedicated Markdown presentation contracts.\n- Strict spec validation passes for this folder.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |","lineStart":40,"lineEnd":129,"totalLines":142,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/003-router-rewire/spec.md","time":{"start":1781143465922,"end":1781143465936}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03ec4f80a3b416b1016a2a17a9d76481918c44e24fb93525c0"}},"id":"prt_eb46c6f98001Hz9wvB4P1z2Ao9","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","messageID":"msg_eb46c4197001LrzhW8VrRpjurM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143465938,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_LUPXsPCGkm16jJjSVII2vTbK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/004-verify-and-ux/implementation-summary.md","offset":40,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/004-verify-and-ux/implementation-summary.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n40: ## Metadata\n41: \n42: | Field | Value |\n43: |-------|-------|\n44: | **Spec Folder** | system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/004-verify-and-ux |\n45: | **Completed** | 2026-06-10 |\n46: | **Level** | 1 |\n47: | **Status** | Completed |\n48: | **Completion** | 100% |\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: <!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->\n54: ## What Was Built\n55: \n56: Captured the memory-family UX contract in presentation Markdown, with special focus on `/memory:search`.\n57: \n58: ### Memory Search UX Change\n59: \n60: - Empty startup now asks one open-ended question: `What would you like to retrieve or analyze?`\n61: - Intent is inferred from the query or delegated to the server when no explicit `--intent:` is provided.\n62: - Targeted follow-up questions are reserved for genuinely missing subcommand parameters.\n63: - Retrieval output is compact, grouped by leaf folder, and limited to score, id, and title unless trace is requested.\n64: - Empty-result fallback uses canonical labels for trigger-matched spec-doc records and constitutional rules.\n65: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: <!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n70: ## How It Was Delivered\n71: \n72: The UX contract is encoded in `search_presentation.md`, while save/manage/learn display consistency is covered in their own presentation assets.\n73: <!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: <!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n78: ## Key Decisions\n79: \n80: | Decision | Why |\n81: |----------|-----|\n82: | Use open-ended startup for search | The operator requested smarter intent inference and fewer startup options. |\n83: | Use compact result tables | Dispatched models need parseable output with low clutter. |\n84: | Keep analysis overview on request | Full menus are useful when asked for, but should not be the default startup path. |\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: <!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n90: ## Verification\n91: \n92: | Check | Result |\n93: |-------|--------|\n94: | Search startup contract | Open-ended question present in `search_presentation.md` and router references it |\n95: | Result-display contract | Compact templates present for retrieval, empty results, and analysis modes |\n96: | Forbidden-label gate | Legacy result labels are described without being emitted as renderable output |\n97: | Strict validation | See final validation output |\n98: <!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: <!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n103: ## Known Limitations\n104: \n105: 1. Cross-model runtime execution was represented by static contract checks in this pass; no external model dispatch was run.\n106: <!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->\n\n(End of file - total 106 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## Metadata\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Spec Folder** | system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/004-verify-and-ux |\n| **Completed** | 2026-06-10 |\n| **Level** | 1 |\n| **Status** | Completed |\n| **Completion** | 100% |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->\n## What Was Built\n\nCaptured the memory-family UX contract in presentation Markdown, with special focus on `/memory:search`.\n\n### Memory Search UX Change\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/004-verify-and-ux/implementation-summary.md","text":"## Metadata\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Spec Folder** | system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/004-verify-and-ux |\n| **Completed** | 2026-06-10 |\n| **Level** | 1 |\n| **Status** | Completed |\n| **Completion** | 100% |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->\n## What Was Built\n\nCaptured the memory-family UX contract in presentation Markdown, with special focus on `/memory:search`.\n\n### Memory Search UX Change\n\n- Empty startup now asks one open-ended question: `What would you like to retrieve or analyze?`\n- Intent is inferred from the query or delegated to the server when no explicit `--intent:` is provided.\n- Targeted follow-up questions are reserved for genuinely missing subcommand parameters.\n- Retrieval output is compact, grouped by leaf folder, and limited to score, id, and title unless trace is requested.\n- Empty-result fallback uses canonical labels for trigger-matched spec-doc records and constitutional rules.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n## How It Was Delivered\n\nThe UX contract is encoded in `search_presentation.md`, while save/manage/learn display consistency is covered in their own presentation assets.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n## Key Decisions\n\n| Decision | Why |\n|----------|-----|\n| Use open-ended startup for search | The operator requested smarter intent inference and fewer startup options. |\n| Use compact result tables | Dispatched models need parseable output with low clutter. |\n| Keep analysis overview on request | Full menus are useful when asked for, but should not be the default startup path. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n## Verification\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Search startup contract | Open-ended question present in `search_presentation.md` and router references it |\n| Result-display contract | Compact templates present for retrieval, empty results, and analysis modes |\n| Forbidden-label gate | Legacy result labels are described without being emitted as renderable output |\n| Strict validation | See final validation output |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n## Known Limitations\n\n1. Cross-model runtime execution was represented by static contract checks in this pass; no external model dispatch was run.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->","lineStart":40,"lineEnd":106,"totalLines":106,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/001-memory-commands/004-verify-and-ux/implementation-summary.md","time":{"start":1781143465927,"end":1781143465938}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03ec4f80a3b416b1016a2a17a9d7748191afc61c59850bb67d"}},"id":"prt_eb46c6fc4001na5iywnrukapQL","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","messageID":"msg_eb46c4197001LrzhW8VrRpjurM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143465957,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_i53ZO8UBzti3FfpymeYlkofz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\n3: argument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /memory:search\n8: \n9: Thin router for memory retrieval and analysis.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep retrieval and analysis routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n16: | Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md` | Required | Startup question policy, analysis overview, result tables, empty-result fallback, and clean GPT-via-opencode display rules. |\n17: \n18: Before asking startup questions or displaying results, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n19: \n20: ## 2. STARTUP ROUTING\n21: \n22: If `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, ask one open-ended question from the presentation asset. Do not dump the full intent/menu list at startup. Treat a custom answer as the retrieval query.\n23: \n24: If the first token is an analysis subcommand, route to analysis mode.\n25: \n26: Known analysis subcommands:\n27: - `preflight`\n28: - `postflight`\n29: - `history`\n30: - `causal`\n31: - `link`\n32: - `unlink`\n33: - `causal-stats`\n34: - `ablation`\n35: - `dashboard`\n36: \n37: Any other non-empty input routes to retrieval mode. Parse optional `--intent:<type>`; otherwise let the server or local router infer intent from the query.\n38: \n39: ## 3. RETRIEVAL MODE\n40: \n41: 1. Extract `query` and optional intent override.\n42: 2. Prefer `memory_context({ input: query, mode: \"auto\", intent, includeContent: true, enableDedup: true })`.\n43: 3. Use `memory_quick_search` for fast query-only fallback.\n44: 4. Use `memory_search` only when fine-grained search parameters are needed.\n45: 5. Use `memory_match_triggers` as a supplemental fallback, not as a replacement for direct retrieval.\n46: 6. For structural code questions, use the stable code-graph tools before semantic or lexical memory channels when available.\n47: 7. Render compact, parseable output using the presentation asset.\n48: \n49: Supported intents:\n50: - `add_feature`\n51: - `fix_bug`\n52: - `refactor`\n53: - `security_audit`\n54: - `understand`\n55: - `find_spec`\n56: - `find_decision`\n57: \n58: ## 4. ANALYSIS MODE\n59: \n60: | Subcommand | Tool | Purpose |\n61: | --- | --- | --- |\n62: | `preflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | `task_preflight` | Capture epistemic baseline. |\n63: | `postflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | `task_postflight` | Capture learning delta. |\n64: | `history <specFolder>` | `memory_get_learning_history` | Show learning cycles. |\n65: | `causal <memoryId>` | `memory_drift_why` | Trace decision lineage. |\n66: | `link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation>` | `memory_causal_link` | Create causal relation. |\n67: | `unlink <edgeId>` | `memory_causal_unlink` | Remove causal relation. |\n68: | `causal-stats` | `memory_causal_stats` | Show graph coverage. |\n69: | `ablation` | `eval_run_ablation` | Run channel ablation when enabled. |\n70: | `dashboard` | `eval_reporting_dashboard` | Show evaluation trends. |\n71: \n72: ## 5. HARD RULES\n73: \n74: - Do not infer a query from prior conversation when `$ARGUMENTS` is empty; ask the open-ended startup question.\n75: - Ask targeted follow-up questions only when the query is genuinely ambiguous.\n76: - Do not display the old option dump at startup.\n77: - Do not use forbidden memory/result labels listed in the presentation asset.\n78: - Do not open raw SQLite or edit memory DB files.\n79: - Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n80: \n81: ## 6. RELATED COMMANDS\n82: \n83: - `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n84: - `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n85: - `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n86: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.\n\n(End of file - total 86 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\nargument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n---\n\n# /memory:search\n\nThin router for memory retrieval and analysis.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep retrieval and analysis routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md` | Required | Startup question policy, analysis overview, result tables, empty-result fallback, and clean GPT-via-opencode display rules. |\n\nBefore asking startup questions or displaying results, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. STARTUP ROUTING","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md","text":"---\ndescription: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\nargument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n---\n\n# /memory:search\n\nThin router for memory retrieval and analysis.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep retrieval and analysis routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md` | Required | Startup question policy, analysis overview, result tables, empty-result fallback, and clean GPT-via-opencode display rules. |\n\nBefore asking startup questions or displaying results, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. STARTUP ROUTING\n\nIf `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, ask one open-ended question from the presentation asset. Do not dump the full intent/menu list at startup. Treat a custom answer as the retrieval query.\n\nIf the first token is an analysis subcommand, route to analysis mode.\n\nKnown analysis subcommands:\n- `preflight`\n- `postflight`\n- `history`\n- `causal`\n- `link`\n- `unlink`\n- `causal-stats`\n- `ablation`\n- `dashboard`\n\nAny other non-empty input routes to retrieval mode. Parse optional `--intent:<type>`; otherwise let the server or local router infer intent from the query.\n\n## 3. RETRIEVAL MODE\n\n1. Extract `query` and optional intent override.\n2. Prefer `memory_context({ input: query, mode: \"auto\", intent, includeContent: true, enableDedup: true })`.\n3. Use `memory_quick_search` for fast query-only fallback.\n4. Use `memory_search` only when fine-grained search parameters are needed.\n5. Use `memory_match_triggers` as a supplemental fallback, not as a replacement for direct retrieval.\n6. For structural code questions, use the stable code-graph tools before semantic or lexical memory channels when available.\n7. Render compact, parseable output using the presentation asset.\n\nSupported intents:\n- `add_feature`\n- `fix_bug`\n- `refactor`\n- `security_audit`\n- `understand`\n- `find_spec`\n- `find_decision`\n\n## 4. ANALYSIS MODE\n\n| Subcommand | Tool | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `preflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | `task_preflight` | Capture epistemic baseline. |\n| `postflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | `task_postflight` | Capture learning delta. |\n| `history <specFolder>` | `memory_get_learning_history` | Show learning cycles. |\n| `causal <memoryId>` | `memory_drift_why` | Trace decision lineage. |\n| `link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation>` | `memory_causal_link` | Create causal relation. |\n| `unlink <edgeId>` | `memory_causal_unlink` | Remove causal relation. |\n| `causal-stats` | `memory_causal_stats` | Show graph coverage. |\n| `ablation` | `eval_run_ablation` | Run channel ablation when enabled. |\n| `dashboard` | `eval_reporting_dashboard` | Show evaluation trends. |\n\n## 5. HARD RULES\n\n- Do not infer a query from prior conversation when `$ARGUMENTS` is empty; ask the open-ended startup question.\n- Ask targeted follow-up questions only when the query is genuinely ambiguous.\n- Do not display the old option dump at startup.\n- Do not use forbidden memory/result labels listed in the presentation asset.\n- Do not open raw SQLite or edit memory DB files.\n- Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n\n## 6. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n- `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n- `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":86,"totalLines":86,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/search.md","time":{"start":1781143465954,"end":1781143465955}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03ec4f80a3b416b1016a2a17a9d77c8191bc76248b101896ab"}},"id":"prt_eb46c6fcb001qapg4eRyf5kXuv","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","messageID":"msg_eb46c4197001LrzhW8VrRpjurM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143465966,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FTSzLE9m1VoJO7GRBDbzpHhO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","offset":1,"limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\n3: argument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /memory:manage\n8: \n9: Thin router for indexed-continuity database management.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep management routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n16: | Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/manage_presentation.md` | Required | Stats, scan, cleanup, retention, tier, trigger, validation, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest, and error displays. |\n17: \n18: Before rendering any dashboard, confirmation prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n19: \n20: ## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n21: \n22: Default mode is `stats` when `$ARGUMENTS` is empty.\n23: \n24: Recognized modes:\n25: - `stats`\n26: - `scan [--force]`\n27: - `cleanup`\n28: - `retention-sweep [--dry-run]`\n29: - `bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]`\n30: - `tier <id> <tier>`\n31: - `triggers <id>`\n32: - `validate <id> <useful|not>`\n33: - `delete <id>`\n34: - `health`\n35: - `checkpoint create|restore|list|delete <name>`\n36: - `ingest start|status|cancel ...`\n37: \n38: On an unknown mode, return `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Unknown mode: <mode>\"` and list the valid modes.\n39: \n40: ## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n41: \n42: | Mode | Primary Tooling | Confirmation |\n43: | --- | --- | --- |\n44: | `stats` | `memory_stats` plus `memory_list` | No |\n45: | `scan` | `memory_index_scan` | Yes |\n46: | `cleanup` | `memory_list`, `checkpoint_create`, `memory_delete` | Yes |\n47: | `retention-sweep` | `memory_retention_sweep` | Yes for mutating sweep |\n48: | `bulk-delete` | `memory_bulk_delete` | Yes |\n49: | `tier` | `memory_update` | No |\n50: | `triggers` | `memory_update` | User saves explicitly |\n51: | `validate` | `memory_validate` | No |\n52: | `delete` | `memory_delete` | Yes |\n53: | `health` | `memory_health` | No |\n54: | `checkpoint` | checkpoint tools | Restore/delete require confirmation |\n55: | `ingest` | ingest tools | Cancel requires explicit job id |\n56: \n57: ## 4. HARD RULES\n58: \n59: - Never query the database with Bash or raw `sqlite3`.\n60: - All database access goes through the allowed MCP tools.\n61: - Do not fall back to raw SQL when MCP fails; report the MCP error and operator fallback guidance.\n62: - Protected tiers require the confirmation gates described in the presentation asset.\n63: - Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n64: \n65: ## 5. RELATED COMMANDS\n66: \n67: - `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n68: - `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n69: - `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n70: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.\n\n(End of file - total 70 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\nargument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n---\n\n# /memory:manage\n\nThin router for indexed-continuity database management.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep management routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/manage_presentation.md` | Required | Stats, scan, cleanup, retention, tier, trigger, validation, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest, and error displays. |\n\nBefore rendering any dashboard, confirmation prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","text":"---\ndescription: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\nargument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n---\n\n# /memory:manage\n\nThin router for indexed-continuity database management.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep management routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/manage_presentation.md` | Required | Stats, scan, cleanup, retention, tier, trigger, validation, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest, and error displays. |\n\nBefore rendering any dashboard, confirmation prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDefault mode is `stats` when `$ARGUMENTS` is empty.\n\nRecognized modes:\n- `stats`\n- `scan [--force]`\n- `cleanup`\n- `retention-sweep [--dry-run]`\n- `bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]`\n- `tier <id> <tier>`\n- `triggers <id>`\n- `validate <id> <useful|not>`\n- `delete <id>`\n- `health`\n- `checkpoint create|restore|list|delete <name>`\n- `ingest start|status|cancel ...`\n\nOn an unknown mode, return `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Unknown mode: <mode>\"` and list the valid modes.\n\n## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n\n| Mode | Primary Tooling | Confirmation |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `stats` | `memory_stats` plus `memory_list` | No |\n| `scan` | `memory_index_scan` | Yes |\n| `cleanup` | `memory_list`, `checkpoint_create`, `memory_delete` | Yes |\n| `retention-sweep` | `memory_retention_sweep` | Yes for mutating sweep |\n| `bulk-delete` | `memory_bulk_delete` | Yes |\n| `tier` | `memory_update` | No |\n| `triggers` | `memory_update` | User saves explicitly |\n| `validate` | `memory_validate` | No |\n| `delete` | `memory_delete` | Yes |\n| `health` | `memory_health` | No |\n| `checkpoint` | checkpoint tools | Restore/delete require confirmation |\n| `ingest` | ingest tools | Cancel requires explicit job id |\n\n## 4. HARD RULES\n\n- Never query the database with Bash or raw `sqlite3`.\n- All database access goes through the allowed MCP tools.\n- Do not fall back to raw SQL when MCP fails; report the MCP error and operator fallback guidance.\n- Protected tiers require the confirmation gates described in the presentation asset.\n- Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n\n## 5. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n- `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n- `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":70,"totalLines":70,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","time":{"start":1781143465964,"end":1781143465966}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03ec4f80a3b416b1016a2a17a9d7848191be5cacb24c10043a"}},"id":"prt_eb46c6fe4001zX3SWHUr7hHHa9","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","messageID":"msg_eb46c4197001LrzhW8VrRpjurM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143465993,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_P1OGNq9iA67oQAqeL4j5xVo1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\n3: argument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /memory:learn\n8: \n9: Thin router for constitutional rule management.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep constitutional-rule routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n16: | Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/learn_presentation.md` | Required | Overview, list, budget, create, edit, remove, confirmation, and result displays. |\n17: \n18: Before rendering any dashboard, approval prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n19: \n20: ## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n21: \n22: Destination: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/`.\n23: \n24: Inputs:\n25: - Empty arguments route to overview.\n26: - `list` routes to constitutional rule list.\n27: - `budget` routes to token budget dashboard.\n28: - `edit <filename>` edits an existing constitutional rule.\n29: - `remove <filename>` removes an existing constitutional rule after confirmation.\n30: - Any other text is treated as a proposed new constitutional rule.\n31: \n32: Outputs:\n33: - `STATUS=OK ACTION=<overview|created|listed|edited|removed|budget>`\n34: - `STATUS=CANCELLED ACTION=<action>`\n35: - `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"<message>\"`\n36: \n37: ## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n38: \n39: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` and choose one route.\n40: 2. For `edit` or `remove` without a filename, list available files and ask one targeted selection question.\n41: 3. For create, verify the rule qualifies as constitutional; suggest `/memory:save` for scoped/session context.\n42: 4. For create/edit/remove, preserve ANCHOR tags and frontmatter shape.\n43: 5. Index changes through `memory_save` or `memory_index_scan` as appropriate.\n44: 6. Verify constitutional visibility with `memory_search` when a new rule is created.\n45: 7. Render all displays from the presentation asset.\n46: \n47: ## 4. HARD RULES\n48: \n49: - Do not infer rule content from screenshots, open files, or prior conversation context.\n50: - Show generated constitutional rule content and wait for approval before writing a new rule.\n51: - For removal, validate filename is basename-only and wait for explicit confirmation.\n52: - Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n53: \n54: ## 5. RELATED COMMANDS\n55: \n56: - `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n57: - `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n58: - `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n59: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.\n\n(End of file - total 59 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\nargument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# /memory:learn\n\nThin router for constitutional rule management.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep constitutional-rule routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/learn_presentation.md` | Required | Overview, list, budget, create, edit, remove, confirmation, and result displays. |\n\nBefore rendering any dashboard, approval prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","text":"---\ndescription: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\nargument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# /memory:learn\n\nThin router for constitutional rule management.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep constitutional-rule routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/learn_presentation.md` | Required | Overview, list, budget, create, edit, remove, confirmation, and result displays. |\n\nBefore rendering any dashboard, approval prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDestination: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/`.\n\nInputs:\n- Empty arguments route to overview.\n- `list` routes to constitutional rule list.\n- `budget` routes to token budget dashboard.\n- `edit <filename>` edits an existing constitutional rule.\n- `remove <filename>` removes an existing constitutional rule after confirmation.\n- Any other text is treated as a proposed new constitutional rule.\n\nOutputs:\n- `STATUS=OK ACTION=<overview|created|listed|edited|removed|budget>`\n- `STATUS=CANCELLED ACTION=<action>`\n- `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"<message>\"`\n\n## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` and choose one route.\n2. For `edit` or `remove` without a filename, list available files and ask one targeted selection question.\n3. For create, verify the rule qualifies as constitutional; suggest `/memory:save` for scoped/session context.\n4. For create/edit/remove, preserve ANCHOR tags and frontmatter shape.\n5. Index changes through `memory_save` or `memory_index_scan` as appropriate.\n6. Verify constitutional visibility with `memory_search` when a new rule is created.\n7. Render all displays from the presentation asset.\n\n## 4. HARD RULES\n\n- Do not infer rule content from screenshots, open files, or prior conversation context.\n- Show generated constitutional rule content and wait for approval before writing a new rule.\n- For removal, validate filename is basename-only and wait for explicit confirmation.\n- Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n\n## 5. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n- `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n- `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":59,"totalLines":59,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","time":{"start":1781143465991,"end":1781143465993}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03ec4f80a3b416b1016a2a17a9d788819187bffbbf00c131ac"}},"id":"prt_eb46c6fec001xl1FM24F0249Dy","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","messageID":"msg_eb46c4197001LrzhW8VrRpjurM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143466048,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_uRz9ec0n3x6nZBNvW5quzRAX","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Memory Search Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Single source of truth for `/memory:search` startup questions, analysis dashboards, and result displays.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Question Policy\n6: \n7: When `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, ask one open-ended question:\n8: \n9: ```text\n10: What would you like to retrieve or analyze?\n11: ```\n12: \n13: Accept any natural-language answer as the retrieval query. Do not dump the full intent or subcommand menu at startup.\n14: \n15: Ask a targeted follow-up only when genuinely ambiguous:\n16: \n17: | Ambiguity | Targeted question |\n18: | --- | --- |\n19: | User asks for `history` without a folder | `Which spec folder should I show learning history for?` |\n20: | User asks for `causal` without an id | `Which spec-doc record ID should I trace?` |\n21: | User asks for `preflight` or `postflight` without required fields | `Which spec folder and task id should I use?` |\n22: | User says `dashboard` or `ablation` | Route directly to analysis mode. |\n23: \n24: If the user asks what is available, show the analysis overview in Section 5.\n25: \n26: ## 2. Retrieval Result Display\n27: \n28: Use compact, parseable output for model dispatch. No option dumps, score bars, long previews, or hidden metadata unless trace was requested.\n29: \n30: ```text\n31: MEMORY:SEARCH \"<query>\" intent=<detected_intent> results=<count>\n32: --------------------------------------------------\n33: <leaf-folder>/\n34:   <score>  #<id>  <title>\n35:   <score>  #<id>  <title>\n36: \n37: <leaf-folder>/\n38:   <score>  #<id>  <title>\n39: \n40: STATUS=OK RESULTS=<count> INTENT=<detected_intent>\n41: ```\n42: \n43: Folder display rules:\n44: - Group by spec folder.\n45: - Show only the leaf folder name unless two leaves collide.\n46: - Each result line shows only score, id, and title.\n47: - Include trace/provenance only when requested or needed to explain a degraded result.\n48: \n49: ## 3. Empty Result Fallback\n50: \n51: ```text\n52: MEMORY:SEARCH \"<query>\" intent=<detected_intent> results=0\n53: --------------------------------------------------\n54: No spec-doc records matched this query via semantic or lexical search.\n55: \n56: Trigger-matched spec-doc records\n57:   <leaf-folder>/\n58:     #<id>  <title>\n59: \n60: Constitutional rules\n61:   #<id>  <title>\n62: \n63: STATUS=OK RESULTS=0 TRIGGERED=<n> CONSTITUTIONAL=<n>\n64: ```\n65: \n66: After the block, ask at most one clarifying follow-up if the query was broad.\n67: \n68: ## 4. Forbidden Vocabulary\n69: \n70: Never emit legacy labels that combine trigger wording with the generic noun `memory` or `memories`, and never label constitutional rows with the generic noun `memory` or `memories`.\n71: \n72: Required labels:\n73: - Trigger fallback rows: `Trigger-matched spec-doc records` or `Trigger-matched spec-doc record`.\n74: - Constitutional rows: `Constitutional rules` or `Constitutional rule`.\n75: - Generic result-class label: `Spec-doc record`.\n76: \n77: Pre-render gate: scan the candidate output case-insensitively for legacy trigger labels and legacy constitutional-result labels, then rewrite them before emitting.\n78: \n79: ## 5. Analysis Overview\n80: \n81: Show only when requested or when the user selected analysis tools.\n82: \n83: ```text\n84: MEMORY:SEARCH ANALYSIS\n85: --------------------------------------------------\n86: Epistemic\n87:   preflight <specFolder> <taskId>\n88:   postflight <specFolder> <taskId>\n89:   history <specFolder>\n90: \n\n(Showing lines 1-90 of 243. Use offset=91 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Memory Search Presentation Contract\n\nSingle source of truth for `/memory:search` startup questions, analysis dashboards, and result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Question Policy\n\nWhen `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, ask one open-ended question:\n\n```text\nWhat would you like to retrieve or analyze?\n```\n\nAccept any natural-language answer as the retrieval query. Do not dump the full intent or subcommand menu at startup.\n\nAsk a targeted follow-up only when genuinely ambiguous:\n\n| Ambiguity | Targeted question |\n| --- | --- |\n| User asks for `history` without a folder | `Which spec folder should I show learning history for?` |\n| User asks for `causal` without an id | `Which spec-doc record ID should I trace?` |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md","text":"# Memory Search Presentation Contract\n\nSingle source of truth for `/memory:search` startup questions, analysis dashboards, and result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Question Policy\n\nWhen `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, ask one open-ended question:\n\n```text\nWhat would you like to retrieve or analyze?\n```\n\nAccept any natural-language answer as the retrieval query. Do not dump the full intent or subcommand menu at startup.\n\nAsk a targeted follow-up only when genuinely ambiguous:\n\n| Ambiguity | Targeted question |\n| --- | --- |\n| User asks for `history` without a folder | `Which spec folder should I show learning history for?` |\n| User asks for `causal` without an id | `Which spec-doc record ID should I trace?` |\n| User asks for `preflight` or `postflight` without required fields | `Which spec folder and task id should I use?` |\n| User says `dashboard` or `ablation` | Route directly to analysis mode. |\n\nIf the user asks what is available, show the analysis overview in Section 5.\n\n## 2. Retrieval Result Display\n\nUse compact, parseable output for model dispatch. No option dumps, score bars, long previews, or hidden metadata unless trace was requested.\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH \"<query>\" intent=<detected_intent> results=<count>\n--------------------------------------------------\n<leaf-folder>/\n  <score>  #<id>  <title>\n  <score>  #<id>  <title>\n\n<leaf-folder>/\n  <score>  #<id>  <title>\n\nSTATUS=OK RESULTS=<count> INTENT=<detected_intent>\n```\n\nFolder display rules:\n- Group by spec folder.\n- Show only the leaf folder name unless two leaves collide.\n- Each result line shows only score, id, and title.\n- Include trace/provenance only when requested or needed to explain a degraded result.\n\n## 3. Empty Result Fallback\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH \"<query>\" intent=<detected_intent> results=0\n--------------------------------------------------\nNo spec-doc records matched this query via semantic or lexical search.\n\nTrigger-matched spec-doc records\n  <leaf-folder>/\n    #<id>  <title>\n\nConstitutional rules\n  #<id>  <title>\n\nSTATUS=OK RESULTS=0 TRIGGERED=<n> CONSTITUTIONAL=<n>\n```\n\nAfter the block, ask at most one clarifying follow-up if the query was broad.\n\n## 4. Forbidden Vocabulary\n\nNever emit legacy labels that combine trigger wording with the generic noun `memory` or `memories`, and never label constitutional rows with the generic noun `memory` or `memories`.\n\nRequired labels:\n- Trigger fallback rows: `Trigger-matched spec-doc records` or `Trigger-matched spec-doc record`.\n- Constitutional rows: `Constitutional rules` or `Constitutional rule`.\n- Generic result-class label: `Spec-doc record`.\n\nPre-render gate: scan the candidate output case-insensitively for legacy trigger labels and legacy constitutional-result labels, then rewrite them before emitting.\n\n## 5. Analysis Overview\n\nShow only when requested or when the user selected analysis tools.\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH ANALYSIS\n--------------------------------------------------\nEpistemic\n  preflight <specFolder> <taskId>\n  postflight <specFolder> <taskId>\n  history <specFolder>\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":90,"totalLines":243,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143466045,"end":1781143466047}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03ec4f80a3b416b1016a2a17a9d7908191a28541197cd16b56"}},"id":"prt_eb46c700b0012S2ckW8h3XljyP","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeS9sQY1uDV505eH","messageID":"msg_eb46c4197001LrzhW8VrRpjurM"}}
